address: Jalan Pucak Manik, Wanagiri, Kec. Sukasada, Kabupaten Buleleng, Bali 81161, Indonesia
review 1: One of my favorite waterfalls in Bali. Never many people, 3 different waterfall types, the walk down isn‚Äôt bad at all, going back up is tiring but always worth it. I‚Äôd guess it only takes about 20-25 mins to get back up.
review 2:
Beautiful and lesser known must visit

Fees 40k less than 2$ (For maintenance, keeping  it safe and keep it clean )

Crowd  : Not well known hence you have entire waterfall to yourself hardly anyone comes.

Level : Easy to moderate has 400 steps sometime steep avoid if you have knee issue. Easy for moderately fit person . Go slow if you getting tired.

Has 4 waterfall (1 has very less water now in august)

1 you can swim too.

There is washroom and bike parking on the top.
review 3:
Definitely underrated. People should come here. The access is very well maintained, including the stairs to go down the hill. Although the track is a bit challenging; rather longer and steeper than others in the area; the view is amazing and very pristine. There are 3-4 photo spots along the track, you can get instagrammable pictures here as well.

Ticket is 20k/person, but it's basically pay 1 get 3 waterfalls.

Bonus: Kiyul (the dog) was our super cute and energetic guide
